Users can define a custom theme in .drift/theme.xml. This is a FULL override — all 18 elements must be specified as <element id="X" color="Y" bold="true" dim="true"/> entries; no inheritance from built-in themes. If any element is missing, the file is rejected with an error naming the first missing element. Precedence: .drift/theme.xml (if exists and valid) overrides --theme=NAME, which overrides the default. If the file exists but fails to parse, drift falls back to the selected built-in theme. See <ref spec="output.theme_system">theme system</ref> and <ref spec="output_impl.theme_loader">theme loader</ref>.